WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.441 --> 00:00:11.820
I feel fucking ridiculous.

2
00:00:11.924 --> 00:00:13.303
You look fucking ridiculous.

3
00:00:13.441 --> 00:00:14.993
You know. I was thinking
you could come to the 10-Petal

4
00:00:15.131 --> 00:00:16.372
- and help out on the weekends.
- Yeah. that sounds cool.

5
00:00:16.475 --> 00:00:18.372
Okay. I want you
to have fun tonight.

6
00:00:18.475 --> 00:00:20.303
♪ tense. dramatic music ♪

7
00:00:20.441 --> 00:00:21.441
[Zane]
<i>There she is.</i>

8
00:00:21.544 --> 00:00:22.441
This is my husband Rip.

9
00:00:22.544 --> 00:00:23.751
Heard a lot about you.

10
00:00:23.855 --> 00:00:24.889
I'm happy
we're in business together.

11
00:00:24.993 --> 00:00:26.303
Business part's my wife.

12
00:00:26.441 --> 00:00:28.406
"Joaquin may not be
a Jackson by birth.

13
00:00:28.475 --> 00:00:31.648
but I've seen him
as my own flesh and blood."

14
00:00:31.751 --> 00:00:33.165
Well. what did you
expect me to do?

15
00:00:33.303 --> 00:00:36.337
This ranch is my legacy.
and I'll never let Kino have it.

16
00:00:36.475 --> 00:00:37.648
Them two.

17
00:00:37.751 --> 00:00:39.337
[Frank]
<i>They didn't see it coming.</i>

18
00:00:39.441 --> 00:00:41.096
- but they had it coming.
- [Austin] <i>But they ain't wrong.</i>

19
00:00:41.131 --> 00:00:42.096
10-Petal's dirty.

20
00:00:42.165 --> 00:00:43.579
As of tonight. I intend

21
00:00:43.648 --> 00:00:45.234
to pass the reins on

22
00:00:45.303 --> 00:00:47.993
to Robert William Jackson III.

23
00:00:48.096 --> 00:00:49.993
- You just fucked yourself.
- Oh. careful now.

24
00:00:50.096 --> 00:00:51.544
Chet always was a lousy shot.

25
00:00:51.648 --> 00:00:53.062
You should've
finished me yourself.

26
00:00:53.131 --> 00:00:54.820
'cause you're never
getting another chance.

27
00:00:54.958 --> 00:00:58.268
You want me? Quit acting like
a fucking steer and grow a pair.

28
00:01:00.062 --> 00:01:01.820
Put that down!

29
00:01:01.924 --> 00:01:03.096
Carter. what the fuck?

30
00:01:03.820 --> 00:01:05.337
[guests gasping]

31
00:01:05.889 --> 00:01:08.096
- Get him out of here.
- [Oreana] Help!

32
00:01:10.510 --> 00:01:12.717
♪ tense. exciting music ♪

33
00:01:19.510 --> 00:01:22.027
[helicopter blades whirring]

34
00:01:47.544 --> 00:01:50.027
[paramedics shouting
indistinctly]

35
00:01:50.855 --> 00:01:52.337
Rob-Will!

36
00:01:59.441 --> 00:02:02.096
Get in.

37
00:02:05.613 --> 00:02:07.958
She's gonna be okay.

38
00:02:13.096 --> 00:02:15.406
[paramedic]
She's in. Let's go!

39
00:02:23.027 --> 00:02:25.200
♪

40
00:02:49.337 --> 00:02:51.579
♪ slow. somber music ♪

41
00:02:52.889 --> 00:02:55.096
[Carter groaning]

42
00:02:56.924 --> 00:02:59.131
[coughs]

43
00:03:04.820 --> 00:03:06.406
[sniffles]

44
00:03:10.648 --> 00:03:12.993
[groaning]

45
00:03:13.820 --> 00:03:16.027
Oh. I'm sorry.

46
00:03:16.165 --> 00:03:18.786
- I'm sorry. [wheezes]
- Carter.

47
00:03:18.855 --> 00:03:20.475
Get up and get on your horse.

48
00:03:20.579 --> 00:03:22.096
Sorry.

49
00:03:22.165 --> 00:03:23.682
So sorry.

50
00:03:23.786 --> 00:03:25.613
- I fucked up.
- Carter.

51
00:03:26.406 --> 00:03:28.406
Get back on your horse.

52
00:03:29.268 --> 00:03:31.027
[Carter sighs]

53
00:03:36.510 --> 00:03:39.579
Come on. get it together now.

54
00:03:48.924 --> 00:03:51.096
[Carter gasps]

55
00:03:53.165 --> 00:03:56.062
I need my... I need my rein.

56
00:03:56.165 --> 00:03:57.751
[Rip]
Here.

57
00:04:00.544 --> 00:04:02.613
Get your shit together.

58
00:04:10.303 --> 00:04:12.372
[Carter groaning softly]

59
00:04:13.786 --> 00:04:16.372
Oh. Wait. wait.

60
00:04:16.441 --> 00:04:17.993
Fuck. wait. Rip.

61
00:04:20.200 --> 00:04:21.372
Oh. fuck.

62
00:04:21.475 --> 00:04:24.062
It's all over
my fucking horse. Rip.

63
00:04:24.165 --> 00:04:25.131
[groans]

64
00:04:25.234 --> 00:04:27.958
Rip. it's all over my horse.

65
00:04:29.579 --> 00:04:31.027
Can we take a break?

66
00:04:31.131 --> 00:04:33.062
Just stay on your fucking horse.

67
00:04:33.165 --> 00:04:36.441
[groaning. coughing]

68
00:04:48.234 --> 00:04:50.889
♪ tense. dramatic music

69
00:04:58.234 --> 00:04:59.993
Sir. you're gonna
have to stay here.

70
00:05:00.062 --> 00:05:01.406
What do we have for access?

71
00:05:01.475 --> 00:05:04.544
We got two 18 AC gauges.
no art-line yet.

72
00:05:04.648 --> 00:05:07.855
[staff speaks indistinctly]

73
00:05:08.682 --> 00:05:10.924
♪ slow. dramatic music

74
00:05:33.062 --> 00:05:36.165
♪

75
00:06:00.096 --> 00:06:02.337
♪

76
00:06:09.406 --> 00:06:11.579
♪ slow. somber music ♪

77
00:06:16.165 --> 00:06:18.337
[footsteps approach]

78
00:06:20.337 --> 00:06:22.544
You get any rest?

79
00:06:23.406 --> 00:06:25.200
No.

80
00:06:25.303 --> 00:06:27.717
He's never acted
that way before.

81
00:06:27.820 --> 00:06:29.406
Shit. Carter's done
a lot of living

82
00:06:29.544 --> 00:06:31.717
- for 19. honey.
- Yeah.

83
00:06:36.165 --> 00:06:38.372
Seems to run in the family.

84
00:06:41.579 --> 00:06:43.717
Hmm.

85
00:06:48.544 --> 00:06:51.717
Yeah. I've broken a lot
of things in my life.

86
00:06:54.372 --> 00:06:56.475
I don't want to break him.

87
00:06:57.303 --> 00:06:59.993
You ain't gonna break Carter. sweetheart.

88
00:07:00.993 --> 00:07:03.441
Remember.
we ain't perfect either.

89
00:07:05.303 --> 00:07:06.820
No.

90
00:07:06.958 --> 00:07:11.303
And we need to teach him
how to be unbreakable.

91
00:07:29.131 --> 00:07:31.200
[elevator bell chimes]

92
00:07:35.510 --> 00:07:36.889
[exhales]

93
00:07:39.648 --> 00:07:41.303
I'm scared. <i>tío.</i>

94
00:07:41.406 --> 00:07:42.579
I know.

95
00:07:42.648 --> 00:07:44.544
Thank you for calling me.

96
00:07:44.648 --> 00:07:46.648
Your family needs you. son.

97
00:07:47.475 --> 00:07:49.027
Glad you're here.

98
00:07:50.096 --> 00:07:51.648
[Oreana sighs]

99
00:07:51.786 --> 00:07:53.131
It's okay.

100
00:07:57.062 --> 00:07:58.441
I made coffee.

101
00:08:01.889 --> 00:08:03.406
I'll be on the porch.

102
00:08:06.441 --> 00:08:08.406
[exhales]

103
00:08:15.717 --> 00:08:17.441
[Carter grunts]

104
00:08:29.165 --> 00:08:31.337
What's going on. baby?

105
00:08:36.924 --> 00:08:38.510
[Carter exhales]

106
00:08:39.510 --> 00:08:41.889
I quit school.

107
00:08:46.441 --> 00:08:47.786
Why?

108
00:08:49.165 --> 00:08:50.924
'Cause.

109
00:08:52.165 --> 00:08:55.200
"'Cause"? Try again.

110
00:08:56.062 --> 00:08:57.131
I hated it.

111
00:08:57.234 --> 00:08:59.200
You hated it.

112
00:08:59.303 --> 00:09:00.303
Okay.

113
00:09:00.372 --> 00:09:02.544
You didn't give it enough time.

114
00:09:02.613 --> 00:09:04.579
- Rip didn't go to school.
- Don't think Rip

115
00:09:04.648 --> 00:09:07.613
had it all sunshine
and fucking roses.

116
00:09:08.475 --> 00:09:10.441
He had nothing.
He had no choice.

117
00:09:10.579 --> 00:09:13.131
You don't just get handed
anything in life.

118
00:09:13.268 --> 00:09:14.682
You got to work for it.

119
00:09:14.786 --> 00:09:18.406
Got to be better. do better.

120
00:09:19.268 --> 00:09:22.062
School can help you learn.
Carter.

121
00:09:22.131 --> 00:09:23.993
Is it the only way? No.

122
00:09:24.096 --> 00:09:27.337
But when you're given a chance
to make your life better.

123
00:09:27.441 --> 00:09:29.441
you fucking grab it.

124
00:09:33.268 --> 00:09:35.924
Carter. I want you happy.

125
00:09:36.717 --> 00:09:39.096
But I need you ready.

126
00:09:39.165 --> 00:09:43.268
Ready for the hard parts when
they come. and they're coming.

127
00:09:46.579 --> 00:09:49.200
I already had two parents die.

128
00:09:49.268 --> 00:09:50.751
I figured that out.

129
00:09:52.303 --> 00:09:54.406
You're right.

130
00:09:55.234 --> 00:09:56.924
But I'm not sure
that's something

131
00:09:57.062 --> 00:10:00.131
you ever figure out. Carter.

132
00:10:01.544 --> 00:10:04.924
And I'm sorry every day
that that happened to you.

133
00:10:15.958 --> 00:10:20.544
My dream is to cowboy.

134
00:10:20.613 --> 00:10:24.786
To be like Rip. like your dad.

135
00:10:26.751 --> 00:10:28.924
[exhales]

136
00:10:30.131 --> 00:10:32.372
♪ slow. somber music

137
00:10:36.717 --> 00:10:38.751
Then you go to work.

138
00:10:41.510 --> 00:10:42.855
Today.

139
00:10:44.096 --> 00:10:47.372
Rip will take you
to the 10-Petal.

140
00:10:47.441 --> 00:10:51.268
Cowboys don't get a day off
'cause they're hungover.

141
00:10:56.234 --> 00:10:59.924
Better hurry up and get dressed.
He won't wait for ya.

142
00:11:02.372 --> 00:11:03.475
Yes. ma'am.

143
00:11:14.786 --> 00:11:16.234
[door closes]

144
00:11:29.924 --> 00:11:31.165
Daddy.

145
00:11:36.027 --> 00:11:38.613
She had a heart attack.
[clears throat]

146
00:11:38.682 --> 00:11:41.820
They. uh. they did
an angioplasty.

147
00:11:41.924 --> 00:11:43.337
Will she live?

148
00:11:43.441 --> 00:11:44.924
She'll be fine.

149
00:11:46.268 --> 00:11:48.475
- When can she come home?
- [chuckles]

150
00:11:48.579 --> 00:11:51.234
Your grandmother's already tried
to escape twice. baby girl.

151
00:11:51.337 --> 00:11:53.200
She's a tough one.

152
00:11:53.337 --> 00:11:55.027
Can I see her?

153
00:11:55.131 --> 00:11:57.648
No. she wants
to talk to us first.

154
00:12:01.544 --> 00:12:02.993
[sniffles]

155
00:12:03.096 --> 00:12:05.062
♪ slow. dramatic music ♪

156
00:12:05.165 --> 00:12:06.544
[door opens]

157
00:12:10.372 --> 00:12:12.924
She's gonna be okay. Oreana.

158
00:12:20.406 --> 00:12:25.441
Kino. I need you to make peace
with your brother.

159
00:12:26.751 --> 00:12:28.303
You lied to me.

160
00:12:29.165 --> 00:12:31.510
No. I-I changed my mind.

161
00:12:31.579 --> 00:12:33.062
I need you to fall in line.

162
00:12:33.165 --> 00:12:35.303
That's the best trick he knows.

163
00:12:35.406 --> 00:12:36.717
And make no mistake.

164
00:12:36.786 --> 00:12:39.268
you need him a lot more
than he needs you.

165
00:12:39.372 --> 00:12:41.268
Well. he's the one
who needs to find a new job.

166
00:12:41.406 --> 00:12:42.924
Oh. stop it.

167
00:12:43.062 --> 00:12:46.544
You're a fine cowboy.
but you're not a true cattleman.

168
00:12:46.613 --> 00:12:47.889
not like Rip Wheeler.

169
00:12:47.993 --> 00:12:49.924
- [laughs softly]
- And you got

170
00:12:50.062 --> 00:12:51.613
a fine head for business. but...

171
00:12:51.717 --> 00:12:53.820
you don't have
Beth's killer instinct.

172
00:12:53.924 --> 00:12:55.096
Well. they're gone. too.

173
00:12:55.234 --> 00:12:59.062
Robert William. you...
[laughs softly]

174
00:12:59.165 --> 00:13:01.441
...you are so goddamned weak.

175
00:13:01.510 --> 00:13:03.613
That's why I'm leaving
the ranch to you.

176
00:13:03.682 --> 00:13:06.717
It's not your prize.
it's your protection.

177
00:13:06.786 --> 00:13:08.579
And Beth and Rip?

178
00:13:08.682 --> 00:13:10.579
They're assets.

179
00:13:10.648 --> 00:13:14.855
so y'all don't end up in here
or somewhere far worse.

180
00:13:18.924 --> 00:13:20.337
You're my sons.

181
00:13:20.441 --> 00:13:22.717
and you're linked at the hip...

182
00:13:23.855 --> 00:13:27.096
...whether you like it or not.
from cradle to grave.

183
00:13:27.165 --> 00:13:28.993
I'll fetch my shovel.

184
00:13:29.958 --> 00:13:31.613
- Enough.
- [Joaquin] Is that all.

185
00:13:31.751 --> 00:13:33.441
Mother?

186
00:13:33.579 --> 00:13:35.234
No.

187
00:13:35.303 --> 00:13:38.475
No. It's fucking everything.

188
00:13:39.751 --> 00:13:41.510
[Joaquin]
Hmm.

189
00:13:41.613 --> 00:13:43.200
[exhales]

190
00:13:45.889 --> 00:13:47.372
Rest up.

191
00:14:04.131 --> 00:14:06.406
[sighs]

192
00:14:09.165 --> 00:14:10.579
First time I cowboyed
with my old man.

193
00:14:10.682 --> 00:14:13.027
I was sore for a week.

194
00:14:13.165 --> 00:14:14.786
Shoot.

195
00:14:14.889 --> 00:14:17.406
Father and son
cowboying side by side.

196
00:14:17.544 --> 00:14:19.200
that's damn beautiful. <i>viejo.</i>

197
00:14:19.303 --> 00:14:21.303
Mm-hmm.

198
00:14:25.131 --> 00:14:27.303
Can't wait to do it with my kid.

199
00:14:27.406 --> 00:14:29.475
Yeah. well.
don't fucking rush. Azul.

200
00:14:29.544 --> 00:14:31.372
Too fucking late.

201
00:14:32.855 --> 00:14:33.958
What's that?

202
00:14:34.062 --> 00:14:36.062
Delilah just found out.

203
00:14:36.165 --> 00:14:38.751
I mean. well.
we-we just found out.

204
00:14:38.855 --> 00:14:40.131
[chuckles]
Congratulations.

205
00:14:40.234 --> 00:14:41.544
- Thanks. boss.
- [Carter coughs]

206
00:14:41.682 --> 00:14:42.751
[Carter]
Whoa. Rip.

207
00:14:42.855 --> 00:14:44.406
[gags]
You got to pull over.

208
00:14:44.510 --> 00:14:46.200
No. no. no. no. don't you
fucking throw up in my truck.

209
00:14:46.337 --> 00:14:47.717
Hold on a second.

210
00:14:51.096 --> 00:14:53.717
[Azul laughs]

211
00:14:53.855 --> 00:14:55.579
Oh. kid's gonna be hating life.

212
00:14:55.717 --> 00:14:57.372
[Rip]
He already does. Look at him.

213
00:14:57.510 --> 00:14:59.889
- Let's go. <i>borrachín.</i>
- What's that one mean?

214
00:14:59.993 --> 00:15:01.441
- What's that mean. now?
- Like a boozehound.

215
00:15:01.579 --> 00:15:02.475
[Rip chuckles]

216
00:15:02.613 --> 00:15:03.717
[Rip]
Come on. now.

217
00:15:03.786 --> 00:15:06.406
Let's go. son. Let's go!

218
00:15:06.475 --> 00:15:09.441
<i>Vámonos.</i>
[laughs]

219
00:15:10.475 --> 00:15:12.337
- Come on. now.
- [Carter grunts] Oh. shit.

220
00:15:12.441 --> 00:15:14.234
[Azul]
Watch out.

221
00:15:14.303 --> 00:15:15.751
You get it out of you?

222
00:15:15.855 --> 00:15:18.062
- Let's go.
- [Azul] <i>Agárrate.</i>

223
00:15:19.786 --> 00:15:21.165
Get in. boy.

224
00:15:25.406 --> 00:15:27.613
♪ hopeful. pastoral music ♪

225
00:15:28.855 --> 00:15:30.717
Right in here.

226
00:15:32.613 --> 00:15:34.131
[knocks on door]

227
00:15:36.786 --> 00:15:38.613
Hi.

228
00:15:42.268 --> 00:15:44.234
Is Carter okay?

229
00:15:44.303 --> 00:15:45.648
He's better now.

230
00:15:48.441 --> 00:15:50.131
Oreana.

231
00:15:51.062 --> 00:15:53.510
Will you help me find
something sweet to eat?

232
00:15:53.613 --> 00:15:56.268
- [Oreana chuckles]
- Please.

233
00:15:57.131 --> 00:16:00.337
- [Oreana] Yeah.
- [Everett] Thanks.

234
00:16:01.165 --> 00:16:03.406
- See you later.
- Thanks.

235
00:16:07.579 --> 00:16:10.372
Ah.

236
00:16:10.441 --> 00:16:12.096
Should've bought you whiskey.

237
00:16:12.165 --> 00:16:13.544
[chuckles]

238
00:16:15.648 --> 00:16:17.475
I'm sorry.

239
00:16:17.579 --> 00:16:21.234
Oh. I've raised boys.

240
00:16:22.096 --> 00:16:24.268
Hell. I'm still raising 'em.

241
00:16:25.337 --> 00:16:26.613
If the worst he's done to date

242
00:16:26.682 --> 00:16:28.855
is a little drunken
hell-raising.

243
00:16:28.958 --> 00:16:30.855
you've done all right by him.

244
00:16:34.786 --> 00:16:36.441
Feels like we're apologizing

245
00:16:36.510 --> 00:16:38.510
for our children
our entire lives.

246
00:16:38.613 --> 00:16:42.268
Maybe we're just apologizing
for ourselves.

247
00:16:42.372 --> 00:16:44.131
Hmm.

248
00:16:45.613 --> 00:16:48.441
Your retirement. Beulah...

249
00:16:50.268 --> 00:16:51.958
...was unexpected.

250
00:16:52.062 --> 00:16:54.510
Yeah. Impulsive maybe.

251
00:16:54.648 --> 00:16:56.027
Little bit.

252
00:16:58.131 --> 00:16:59.475
You know. it changes things.

253
00:16:59.579 --> 00:17:01.406
I don't see how.

254
00:17:02.200 --> 00:17:05.062
10-Petal's stronger
with you and Rip.

255
00:17:05.165 --> 00:17:06.510
whether I'm there or not.

256
00:17:06.613 --> 00:17:09.717
Well. I didn't agree
to work with your son.

257
00:17:09.855 --> 00:17:11.751
I agreed to work with you.

258
00:17:11.855 --> 00:17:14.717
Well. I'm not
leaving tomorrow. so...

259
00:17:14.786 --> 00:17:17.682
if you're willing.
I'd love for you to just

260
00:17:17.786 --> 00:17:19.268
take it a day at a time.

261
00:17:20.131 --> 00:17:24.096
Well. we'll talk about it when
you're out of here. shall we?

262
00:17:25.303 --> 00:17:27.200
You just get better.

263
00:17:29.889 --> 00:17:32.062
But he is a mistake.

264
00:17:33.337 --> 00:17:35.889
He's a liability. Beulah.

265
00:17:35.993 --> 00:17:37.889
He's my son. Beth.

266
00:17:37.958 --> 00:17:42.544
I will not apologize for him
or myself.

267
00:17:42.682 --> 00:17:44.889
