00:37:09.406 --> 00:37:10.751
No.

534
00:37:10.855 --> 00:37:12.855
I just no longer give a fuck.

535
00:37:12.993 --> 00:37:15.441
[phone vibrates]

536
00:37:16.993 --> 00:37:18.131
Hello.

537
00:37:19.234 --> 00:37:20.303
Yeah. hang on.

538
00:37:20.372 --> 00:37:22.268
You can leave that.

539
00:37:22.372 --> 00:37:25.234
and I want you to shut that door
on your way out.

540
00:37:27.303 --> 00:37:28.958
Go on.

541
00:37:34.889 --> 00:37:36.510
["Pipe Dream"
by Red Shahan playing]

542
00:37:36.648 --> 00:37:39.406
<i>♪ Crybaby's graduating ♪</i>

543
00:37:39.544 --> 00:37:43.682
<i>♪ Ship him off.
watch the women run wild...♪</i>

544
00:37:45.544 --> 00:37:48.062
Beer and two shots of Jack.

545
00:37:48.200 --> 00:37:50.406
<i>♪ Foresee the pipe dream ♪</i>

546
00:37:50.544 --> 00:37:53.544
<i>♪ Didn't change a thing ♪</i>

547
00:37:54.786 --> 00:37:56.027
<i>♪ Those trophies ain't gold... ♪</i>

548
00:37:56.165 --> 00:37:58.406
What'd you go to prison for?

549
00:37:58.510 --> 00:38:01.131
That's an impolite question.

550
00:38:01.268 --> 00:38:03.062
That's why I'm asking.

551
00:38:03.165 --> 00:38:04.475
Hmm.

552
00:38:05.820 --> 00:38:07.682
I was drunk...

553
00:38:08.441 --> 00:38:10.855
...had a fight
with my girl Terry Jane.

554
00:38:10.958 --> 00:38:13.475
Put my pickup in reverse

555
00:38:13.613 --> 00:38:15.751
and didn't realize
she'd followed me out

556
00:38:15.855 --> 00:38:17.820
till it was too late.

557
00:38:18.682 --> 00:38:21.234
<i>♪ Find a friend
that's nothing like you...♪</i>

558
00:38:21.303 --> 00:38:23.096
Got another question.

559
00:38:23.200 --> 00:38:24.613
Shoot.

560
00:38:25.475 --> 00:38:30.027
<i>♪ Turn your back
on who you've been ♪</i>

561
00:38:31.993 --> 00:38:35.062
<i>♪ Midnight oil
in a cotton field ♪</i>

562
00:38:35.131 --> 00:38:37.234
Can I fucking trust you?

563
00:38:38.165 --> 00:38:42.889
<i>♪ Stirrin' up trouble
with a broken seal...♪</i>

564
00:38:42.958 --> 00:38:45.579
Can I fucking trust Rip?

565
00:38:47.475 --> 00:38:49.234
With your life.

566
00:38:50.958 --> 00:38:53.751
♪ slow. tense music

567
00:39:01.993 --> 00:39:03.303
[sniffles]

568
00:39:19.027 --> 00:39:21.682
[footsteps approaching]

569
00:39:24.165 --> 00:39:25.372
You want to talk?

570
00:39:26.200 --> 00:39:27.958
What happened to Xena?

571
00:39:29.441 --> 00:39:33.200
She's at that Texas Zoofari Park
down in Kaufman.

572
00:39:33.337 --> 00:39:35.337
Didn't shoot her. too?

573
00:39:36.268 --> 00:39:37.475
Careful.

574
00:39:38.682 --> 00:39:41.544
You only get to question
my integrity once.

575
00:39:44.062 --> 00:39:45.751
It's good to see you sobered up.

576
00:39:47.303 --> 00:39:49.234
You done making a fool
of yourself?

577
00:39:54.855 --> 00:39:56.337
I want a job.

578
00:39:56.441 --> 00:39:57.820
Try the unemployment office.

579
00:39:57.924 --> 00:40:00.786
No. I want a job with you.

580
00:40:00.889 --> 00:40:02.544
Of course.

581
00:40:02.648 --> 00:40:05.165
[chuckles]

582
00:40:05.268 --> 00:40:06.958
You need a GED

583
00:40:07.062 --> 00:40:10.406
or a diploma. plus
a Basic Peace Officer Course.

584
00:40:10.510 --> 00:40:12.131
Do I?

585
00:40:12.889 --> 00:40:15.682
I think if Dwight White were
here. he'd think differently.

586
00:40:15.855 --> 00:40:18.062
♪ slow. dramatic music ♪

587
00:40:19.579 --> 00:40:21.096
Go home. son.

588
00:40:21.855 --> 00:40:23.786
There's nothing for you
around here.

589
00:40:49.200 --> 00:40:50.820
[Austin]
<i>Something's always felt off.</i>

590
00:40:50.889 --> 00:40:52.820
Like the way they still
brought in big cattle loads

591
00:40:52.889 --> 00:40:55.165
after the border got shut down
'cause of screwworm.

592
00:40:55.303 --> 00:40:57.510
And you know this for sure?

593
00:40:58.337 --> 00:41:01.131
Wes wanted to get
to the bottom of it.

594
00:41:01.234 --> 00:41:04.441
buddied up to Rob-Will.
then ended up dead.

595
00:41:04.544 --> 00:41:06.510
The bottom of what?

596
00:41:08.337 --> 00:41:10.303
10-Petal's got an operation
down in Mexico

597
00:41:10.406 --> 00:41:13.200
that steals and smuggles
cattle in illegally.

598
00:41:14.062 --> 00:41:15.544
Forges all the paperwork
for Border Patrol

599
00:41:15.648 --> 00:41:17.648
and cattle brokers.

600
00:41:17.751 --> 00:41:19.579
Place is so mismanaged.

601
00:41:19.682 --> 00:41:21.579
it's the only way
they've kept the lights on.

602
00:41:21.717 --> 00:41:23.717
kept living in luxury.

603
00:41:23.786 --> 00:41:25.717
I mean. hell. it's the only way
they've been able to afford

604
00:41:25.855 --> 00:41:27.234
a goddamn thing.

605
00:41:27.337 --> 00:41:30.337
Whole Jackson family's crooked.
top to bottom.

606
00:41:33.717 --> 00:41:35.303
They ain't ranchers.

607
00:41:35.406 --> 00:41:36.751
Those motherfuckers are thieves.

608
00:41:36.889 --> 00:41:39.406
putting every ranch
in South Texas at risk.

609
00:41:39.510 --> 00:41:41.372
[Zach sighs]
That would explain

610
00:41:41.475 --> 00:41:43.027
Bullet.

611
00:41:43.820 --> 00:41:45.234
And foot-and-mouth.

612
00:41:46.062 --> 00:41:48.234
When's the next load?

613
00:41:50.234 --> 00:41:51.855
Two days.

614
00:41:53.096 --> 00:41:55.303
♪ tense. dark music

615
00:42:01.062 --> 00:42:02.406
[sighs deeply]

616
00:42:10.268 --> 00:42:12.372
[groaning]

617
00:42:25.786 --> 00:42:27.786
Fuck.

618
00:42:29.303 --> 00:42:32.510
Fuck!

619
00:42:32.613 --> 00:42:35.786
<i>¡Su puta madre!</i>

620
00:42:36.648 --> 00:42:39.786
[breathing heavily]

621
00:42:43.993 --> 00:42:45.268
[grunts]

622
00:42:51.613 --> 00:42:53.717
[exhales]

623
00:42:56.717 --> 00:42:58.924
♪ ominous music ♪

624
00:43:18.579 --> 00:43:20.958
- [phone beeps]
- [inhales deeply]

625
00:43:25.062 --> 00:43:26.648
<i>Hola. papá.</i>

626
00:43:26.751 --> 00:43:29.165
<i>Necesito tu ayuda.</i>

627
00:43:32.062 --> 00:43:35.131
♪
